        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 4:51PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 451 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Sheridan to 13 miles southeast of Harrison
to 12 miles south of Bozeman. Movement was north at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bozeman, Belgrade, Three Forks, Manhattan, Whitehall, Pony, Harrison,
Norris, Bozeman Hot Springs, Gallatin Gateway, Cardwell, Logan, Lewis
And Clark Caverns State Park, Four Corners, Amsterdam, Church Hill,
Willow Creek, and Madison Buffalo Jump State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
